  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen I complete a deployment, I have to manually edit the network ID as it is wrong.\r\n\r\nI deploy on Rinkeby, which is network 3, but when I go to my contract's .JSON on build/contracts, there is \"4\" (which is mainnet) so I have to manually edit it to 3 everytime.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\ntruffle deploy --reset --network rinkeby (which is 3)\r\n\r\n**contents of my truffle.config file:** \r\n```javascript\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n\r\n  networks: {\r\n    development: {\r\n      host: \"localhost\",\r\n      port : 8545,\r\n      network_id: \"*\",\r\n      gas: 6700000\r\n    },\r\n    testnet: {\r\n      provider: function() {\r\n        return new HDWalletProvider(process.env['TESTNETMNEMONIC'], `https://${process.env['TESTNET']}.infura.io/${process.env['INFURATOKEN']}`);\r\n      },\r\n      network_id: 2\r\n    },\r\n    rinkeby: {\r\n      provider: function() {\r\n        return new HDWalletProvider(process.env['RINKEBYNETMNEMONIC'], `https://rinkeby.infura.io/${process.env['INFURATOKEN']}`);\r\n      },\r\n      network_id: 3\r\n    },\r\n    mainnet: {\r\n      provider: function() {\r\n        return new HDWalletProvider(process.env['MAINNETMNEMONIC'], `https://${process.env['MAINNET']}.infura.io/${process.env['INFURATOKEN']}`);\r\n      },\r\n      network_id: 4\r\n    }, solc: {\r\n      optimizer: {\r\n        enabled: true,\r\n        runs: 200\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n};`\r\n```\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nShould write network id 3 instead of 4 on the .JSON file\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\nwindows 10 / truffle v4.1.12 and solidity v0.4.24\r\n\r\n",
